content:
Analytics uses internal users, Integration User and Security User, to access Salesforce data. 
The Integration User's permissions restrict the data extracted from Salesforce only—they don’t affect access to the data in datasets. To restrict user access to data in datasets, set up row-level security.

To enable interactive preview in recipes, Data Prep uses the Security User. The Security User’s permissions don’t affect the data shown in the preview.

Analytics uses the Security User's permissions to access the Salesforce User object and its fields when querying a dataset with row-level security based on the User object.

The Integration User and Security User must not be deleted as they are required for Analytics to function.

title: Internal Analytics Users in Salesforce
